extends layout

block content
  .content-narrow(style='display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px')
    div(style='display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:4px')
      span.label ABOUT
      span.page-title 21 million is the ceiling, not the count.

    .prose
      p
        | Bitcoin's supply is usually quoted as if every coin ever issued still circulates. It doesn't. Some coin is
        span.em-red  provably gone
        |  — spent to conditions that can never be met, or never created because a miner didn't claim it. Some is
        span.em  probably gone
        |  — sent to burn addresses with no known keys. And a large, debatable amount has simply
        span.em  not moved in a decade or more
        | .
      p This site doesn't pick a number for you. Every figure traces to a public classification rule, and the sliders let you decide how much doubt to accept — from mathematical certainty to speculation.

    section.section.section--tight
      span.label HOW TO CONTRIBUTE
      div(style='display:flex;flex-direction:column')
        .step-row
          span.n 01
          span.t Propose a new loss classification: open a PR adding a markdown file to #[a(href='https://github.com/anders94/bitcoin-supply.com-2/tree/main/proposals') proposals/] in the GitHub repo.
        .step-row
          span.n 02
          span.t Debate happens in PR comments. Challenge scale estimates, evidence, and edge cases.
        .step-row
          span.n 03
          span.t Proposals that reach finality are implemented as detectors and their figures appear on this site.
      a.ext-link(href='https://github.com/anders94/bitcoin-supply.com-2') GITHUB.COM/ANDERS94/BITCOIN-SUPPLY.COM-2 →

    section.section.section--tight
      span.label METHODOLOGY
      p(style='margin:0;font-size:11.5px;line-height:1.6;color:var(--body-dark)') Figures are computed from a fully-indexed Bitcoin Core node. Every UTXO is run through the classifier pipeline; dormancy is computed at query time, never stored. Nothing here is an estimate unless labeled as one.

    .credit
      span.by BUILT BY #[a(href='https://andersbrownworth.com') ANDERS BROWNWORTH]
      span.lic MIT LICENSE
